# Design

## Frames and panels

- **No stroke** on cards/panels. Do not use borders for frame separation.
- **Glass effect**: use the `.frame-glass` utility (defined in `src/app/globals.css`) for analysis and dashboard cards. It provides:
  - No border
  - Semi-transparent background (`rgba(255,255,255,0.06)` in dark)
  - `backdrop-filter: blur(12px)` for glassmorphism
- Use `.frame-glass` for all analysis dashboard cards/panels. Add rounded corners via Tailwind (e.g. `rounded-xl`) as needed.

## Colors

- **Accent** `#43D1A7`: use sparingly and in bold splashes (active tab, key metrics, primary CTAs). CSS variable `--accent`; Tailwind `text-accent`, `bg-accent`, etc.
- **Background (dark mode)** `#222631`: main dark background. CSS variable `--background` when `.dark`; Tailwind `bg-background` or `bg-background-dark`.
- **Shot-type colors** (one per shot type, for charts and legends): defined in `globals.css` as `--shot-serve`, `--shot-clear`, etc., and in `src/lib/shot_chart_utils.ts` as `SHOT_TYPE_HEX`. Use for bar fills, donut segments, and legends.

## Typography

- App font is set in `src/app/layout.tsx` (Outfit) and applied via `--font-sans` in `globals.css`. Use the default sans font for UI; keep it consistent across pages.

## Reference

- Token definitions: `src/app/globals.css`
- Shot-type hex map: `SHOT_TYPE_HEX` in `src/lib/shot_chart_utils.ts`
